  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\nexport interface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n#### 3b. **engine.ts** - BuildEngine Class\n\nThe BuildEngine class orchestrates the build process:\n\n- **registerPlugin(plugin: Plugin)**: Adds a plugin to the engine\n- **registerTemplate(template: Template)**: Registers a template for rendering\n- **resolvePluginOrder()**: Topological sort of plugins based on dependencies\n  - Detects circular dependencies\n  - Detects missing dependencies\n  - Returns plugins in execution order\n- **async build(files: ContentFile[])**: Main build method that:\n  1. Creates BuildContext with config, files, output Map, assets Map, data Map\n  2. Resolves plugin execution order\n  3. Executes all `beforeBuild` hooks in order\n  4. Applies `transformContent` hooks to each file sequentially\n  5. Renders content using registered templates (or outputs raw content if no template)\n  6. Executes all `afterBuild` hooks in order\n  7. Returns the populated BuildContext\n- **getPlugins()**: Returns copy of registered plugins\n- **getTemplates()**: Returns copy of registered templates\n\n#### 3c. **templates.ts** - Default Templates\n\n**createDefaultTemplate()**: Single article template with title, time, and content\n- HTML structure with DOCTYPE, head, body\n- Interpolates: title, siteTitle, date, content\n\n**createListTemplate()**: List template for displaying lists of items\n- Similar structure but with `<div class=\"list\">` wrapper\n\n#### 3d. **index.ts** - Public Exports\n\n```typescript\nexport { BuildEngine } from './engine.js';\nexport { createDefaultTemplate, createListTemplate } from './templates.js';\nexport type { BuildContext, ContentFile, Plugin, PluginHooks, SiteConfig, Template } from './types.js';\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Test Files (tests/)\n\n#### 4a. **core.test.ts** - 14 Core Tests\n\nKey test behaviors:\n1. Plugin registration\n2. Template registration  \n3. Default template rendering with HTML\n4. List template rendering\n5. Raw content output when no template\n6. beforeBuild hook execution\n7. transformContent hook (modifies file content)\n8. afterBuild hook execution\n9. Plugin dependency resolution (topological sort)\n10. Circular dependency detection\n11. Missing dependency detection\n12. Multiple plugins applying transformContent in order\n13. Shared data store between plugins\n14. Metadata/date/tags preservation through build\n\n---\n\n#### 4b. **Plugin Test Files** (8 total)\n\nEach test file defines expected behavior for the plugin it tests. Here are the key requirements:\n\n### **search-index.test.ts** (7 tests)\n\nCreates a `createSearchIndexPlugin()` that:\n- Implements `afterBuild` hook\n- Generates `search-index.json` in ctx.output\n- Each index entry has: `slug`, `title`, `content` (plain text)\n- Strips HTML tags from indexed content but preserves text\n- Includes code blocks in searchable text\n- Handles empty file lists\n- Produces valid JSON array\n- Includes `tags` array in entries if present on file\n\n### **markdown-ext.test.ts** (7 tests)\n\nCreates a `createMarkdownExtPlugin()` that:\n- Implements `transformContent` hook\n- Converts markdown to HTML using `marked` library\n- Supports extended markdown syntax:\n  - **Footnotes**: `[^1]` syntax creates `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>`\n  - Renders `<section class=\"footnotes\">` with `<li id=\"fn-N\">` items\n  - **Admonitions**: `:::note`, `:::warning`, `:::tip` containers\n    - Converts to `<div class=\"admonition admonition-{type}\">`\n- Preserves existing HTML content\n- Handles empty content\n\n### **taxonomy.test.ts** (8 tests)\n\nCreates a `createTaxonomyPlugin()` that:\n- Implements both `beforeBuild` and `afterBuild` hooks\n- In `beforeBuild`: builds tag index from file.tags\n  - Stores in `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')` as `Map<string, ContentFile[]>`\n  - Normalizes tags to lowercase\n- In `afterBuild`: generates tag listing pages\n  - Creates files at `tags/{tag}.html`\n  - Each page lists all files with that tag\n- Handles files with no tags\n- Handles files with multiple tags\n- Supports case-insensitive tag matching\n\n### **dev-server.test.ts** (8 tests)\n\nCreates a `createDevServerPlugin()` that:\n- Implements `afterBuild` hook\n- Stores `dev-server-config` in ctx.data with structure:\n  ```\n  {\n    port: number,\n    routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>,\n    assetPaths: string[],\n    searchIndexPath: string\n  }\n  ```\n- Default port is 3000\n- Reads asset-pipeline data from `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')`\n  - Uses asset-manifest.assets array\n  - Creates routes for each asset with handler: \"asset\"\n- Creates static routes for content files (handler: \"static\")\n- Includes search index path from ctx.output (e.g., `/search-index.json`)\n- Handles missing asset-pipeline data gracefully\n\n### **rss-feed.test.ts** (8 tests)\n\nCreates a `createRssFeedPlugin()` that:\n- Implements `afterBuild` hook\n- Generates valid RSS 2.0 XML (`feed.xml`)\n- XML structure: `<?xml...` → `<rss version=\"2.0\">` → `<channel>` → `<item>`\n- Each item contains HTML content wrapped in `<![CDATA[...]]>`\n- Includes category tags from taxonomy (reads `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')`)\n- Channel title from `config.title`\n- Items sorted by date (newest first)\n- Handles files without dates gracefully\n- Links use `config.baseUrl`\n  - Channel link: baseUrl\n  - Item links: `baseUrl/{slug}.html`\n\n### **sitemap.test.ts** (8 tests)\n\nCreates a `createSitemapPlugin()` that:\n- Implements `afterBuild` hook\n- Generates `sitemap.xml` (valid XML structure)\n- Includes all content URLs from ctx.output (*.html files)\n- Includes tag page URLs from taxonomy (reads `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')`)\n  - Format: `{baseUrl}/tags/{tag}.html`\n- Includes feed.xml URL if present\n- Uses `config.baseUrl` for URL construction\n- Valid XML: `<?xml version=\"1.0\"` → `<urlset>` → `<url>` → `<loc>`\n\n### **asset-pipeline.test.ts** (10 tests)\n\nCreates a `createAssetPipelinePlugin()` that:\n- Implements `transformContent` hook\n- Rewrites relative URLs to `/assets/` path:\n  - Image src: `./image.png` → `/assets/image.png`\n  - Link href: `./doc.pdf` → `/assets/doc.pdf`\n- Leaves absolute URLs unchanged (https://, http://)\n- Generates asset manifest in `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')` with structure:\n  ```\n  { assets: string[] }\n  ```\n- Handles multiple assets in one file\n- Accumulates assets across files\n- Does NOT process already-rewritten `/assets/` URLs (no double-processing)\n- Handles files with no asset references\n\n### **syntax-highlight.test.ts** (8 tests)\n\nCreates a `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin()` that:\n- Implements `transformContent` hook\n- Processes `<pre><code class=\"language-{lang}\">` blocks\n- Adds `highlighted` class to code element\n- Adds `data-language=\"{lang}\"` attribute to pre tag\n- Extracts language from `class=\"language-{lang}\"` format\n- Handles multiple code blocks in one file\n- Does NOT process code blocks without language class\n- Preserves code block content exactly\n- Handles empty code blocks\n- Does NOT modify inline `<code>` tags (only pre blocks)\n\n---\n\n### 5. Build Process Flow\n\nThe build system uses a **DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph)** plugin system with these phases:\n\n```\n1. Plugin Registration\n   ↓\n2. Topological Sort (resolve dependencies)\n   ↓\n3. beforeBuild hooks (all plugins)\n   ↓\n4. transformContent hooks (applied to each file in plugin order)\n   ↓\n5. Template rendering (maps ContentFile to HTML output)\n   ↓\n6. afterBuild hooks (all plugins)\n   ↓\n7. Return populated BuildContext\n```\n\nEach plugin gets access to:\n- Full site config\n- Current file list\n- Output map (add rendered content)\n- Assets map (add binary data)\n- Data store (share information between plugins)\n\n---\n\n### 6. Key Plugin Dependencies\n\nBased on test expectations:\n\n```\nasset-pipeline\n    ↑\ndev-server (depends on asset-pipeline for asset paths)\n\nmarkdown-ext (independent)\n\nsearch-index (independent)\n\ntaxonomy (independent)\n\nsyntax-highlight (independent)\n\nrss-feed (depends on taxonomy for categories)\n\nsitemap (depends on taxonomy for tag pages)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nYou need to implement 8 plugins in `/workspace/src/plugins/`:\n\n1. **search-index.ts** - Generate searchable index\n2. **markdown-ext.ts** - Markdown to HTML with extensions\n3. **taxonomy.ts** - Tag management and listing\n4. **dev-server.ts** - Dev server configuration\n5. **rss-feed.ts** - RSS feed generation\n6. **sitemap.ts** - XML sitemap generation\n7. **asset-pipeline.ts** - Asset URL rewriting\n8. **syntax-highlight.ts** - Code block highlighting\n\nEach must export a factory function (e.g., `createSearchIndexPlugin()`) that returns a `Plugin` object with the required hooks and implementations as defined by their test files."}],"totalDurationMs":42146,"totalTokens":35548,"totalToolUseCount":22,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":222,"cache_read_input_tokens":31774,"output_tokens":3549,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":222,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations"